{
  "texts": [
    "Liver Disorders datasets were each used in four papers.",
    "Of the 187 remaining datasets, 70% were publicly available, and 30% were acquired from hospitals and healthcare units.",
    "Based on the findings, the MIT-BIH Arrhythmia Database (Moody and Mark 1980) was the most commonly used dataset, owing to the numerous selected studies in cardiology and its reputation as a well-known benchmark dataset.",
    "The MIT-BIH Arrhythmia Database comprises 48 ECG recordings, each with a duration of 30 min and a sampling frequency of 360 Hz (Shi et al. 2019).",
    "All heartbeats within the recordings are expertly annotated and categorised into one of 15 heartbeat types."
  ]
}